Launched in 2012, the Global Citizen Festival is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international group of anti-poverty activists by increasing the number of people actively fighting poverty.
In order to receive a free ticket to the event (unless you decided to purchase a VIP ticket), concert participants had to complete a number of tasks or “activities” such as volunteering, sending an email to a world leader, making a phone call, or other significant activities to help raise awareness about the goal of ending poverty.
But what successes can Global Citizen boast of in the perspective of 12 years remaining to achieve the goal?
