Global Citizen says it has seen more than 19 million “actions” from campaign supporters since 2011 to pursue a number of different goals.
It also claims that these actions have helped spur world leaders to announce commitments and regulations worth more than $37 billion that are expected to impact the lives of more than 2.25 billion people by 2030.
