The usual host of this long-running show, Kirsty Young, took a few months off due to illness.
Appearing on the show for the first time led by Laverne, Daley said that growing up, he felt "less valuable" than others because "simultaneously liking boys and girls was not socially acceptable."
He said: “To this day, this feeling of being less valuable and different is something that gives me the strength to succeed.”
He said he wanted to prove he was “worth something” so as not to disappoint everyone when they finally found out about his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist became a high-profile LGBT activist and used his performance at this year's Commonwealth Games in Australia to appeal to more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he decided to express himself because he felt happy to live openly, without any implications, and wanted to give others “hope” in this way.
The three-time world champion said he was "surprised" to fall in love with a man - American filmmaker Dustin Lance Black, whom he met in 2013.
